# Component Strategy (Early Stage)

- Build reusable components only.
- Keep components simple and readable.
- Prefer duplication over premature abstraction.
- Do not generalize components too early.
- Focus on matching the UI reference first (layout/structure); pixel-perfect is allowed.
- Refactor later once the structure is validated.
- For components with variants, keep one clear props contract and render from props, not ad-hoc style branches.
- Reuse a shared variant naming scheme across components:
  - `size`: `small | medium | large`
  - booleans like `flush`, `expanded`
  - interaction state keys like `default | hover | pressed | focused` when needed by design review/demo.

# Styling Inside Components

- Use Tailwind for layout/spacing/border/radius/shadow.
- Use semantic color tokens for colors (no hardcoded color values).
- Use the correct typography font utility explicitly (UI vs content) based on the text role.

